  FOUR people, including a driver, have lost their lives and burnt beyond recognition in a head-on crash involving a truck and a car this morning in Limpopo. The deadly accident happened on the R516 road next to Kroomdraai Crossing in the Waterburg District, were both vehicles caught fire after the impact. Matome Moremi-Taueatsoala, the spokesman for the Department of Transport and Community Safety in Limpopo, confirmed that all four deceased were in the car and they burnt beyond recognition. "They include a driver, two passengers, and a child. The truck driver was rushed to the hospital with serious injuries. Preliminary investigations revealed that over speeding and reckless driving were a possible cause of the accident," Moremi-Taueatsoala said.  Moremi-Taueatsoala added that the road is still closed, and motorists are advised to use alternative routes until the scene is cleared.